TITLE: Nix Data Types Example
DESCRIPTION: Comprehensive example showing all primitive data types, lists and attribute sets in Nix.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nixos/nix.dev/blob/master/source/tutorials/nix-language.md#2025-04-16_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: nix
CODE:
```
{
  string = "hello";
  integer = 1;
  float = 3.141;
  bool = true;
  null = null;
  list = [ 1 "two" false ];
  attribute-set = {
    a = "hello";
    b = 2;
    c = 2.718;
    d = false;
  };
}
```

