TITLE: Creating a Simple Nix Package Declaration
DESCRIPTION: A simplified Nixpkgs package declaration that shows how to create a derivation for the GNU Hello program. The code demonstrates function arguments, attribute sets, string interpolation, and the use of fetchurl to download the source code.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nixos/nix.dev/blob/master/source/tutorials/nix-language.md#2025-04-16_snippet_38

LANGUAGE: nix
CODE:
```
{ lib, stdenv, fetchurl }:

stdenv.mkDerivation rec {

  pname = "hello";

  version = "2.12";

  src = fetchurl {
    url = "mirror://gnu/${pname}/${pname}-${version}.tar.gz";
    sha256 = "1ayhp9v4m4rdhjmnl2bq3cibrbqqkgjbl3s7yk2nhlh8vj3ay16g";
  };

  meta = with lib; {
    license = licenses.gpl3Plus;
  };

}
```

