TITLE: Using the override Function for Post-Creation Customization
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the override function to modify package parameters after the initial derivation has been created. This allows for creating variations of packages without duplicate code.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nixos/nix.dev/blob/master/source/tutorials/callpackage.md#2025-04-16_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: nix
CODE:
```
let
  pkgs = import <nixpkgs> { };
in
rec {
  hello = pkgs.callPackage ./hello.nix { audience = "people"; };
  hello-folks = hello.override { audience = "folks"; };
}
```

