TITLE: Configuring Distributed Builds on NixOS Systems
DESCRIPTION: NixOS module for setting up distributed builds on the local machine. This configuration enables distributing builds to remote machines with specific system features support.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nixos/nix.dev/blob/master/source/tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md#2025-04-16_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: nix
CODE:
```
{ pkgs, ... }:
{
  nix.distributedBuilds = true;
  nix.settings.builders-use-substitutes = true;

  nix.buildMachines = [
    {
      hostName = "remotebuilder";
      sshUser = "remotebuild";
      sshKey = "/root/.ssh/remotebuild";
      system = pkgs.stdenv.hostPlatform.system;
      supportedFeatures = [ "nixos-test" "big-parallel" "kvm" ];
    }
  ];
}
```

