TITLE: Build System Impurities List
DESCRIPTION: Markdown list detailing the various impurities that exist in Nix's sandboxed build system, including system-level and environmental factors that can affect build reproducibility
SOURCE: https://github.com/nixos/nix.dev/blob/master/source/concepts/faq.md#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: markdown
CODE:
```
- CPU architecturegreat effort being made to avoid compilation of native instructions in favour of hardcoded supported ones.
- System's current time/date.
- The filesystem used for building (see also `TMPDIR`).
- Linux kernel parameters, such as:
  - IPv6 capabilities.
  - binfmt interpreters, e.g., those configured with `boot.binfmt.emulatedSystems`.
- Timing behaviour of the build systemparallel Make build does not get the correct inputs in some cases.
- Insertion of random values, e.g., from /dev/random or /dev/urandom.
- Differences between Nix versions.
```

